{
  "stem": "8370.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you know, it's almost every day, almost every day.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, there have been periods when you had train after train coming.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's what I told you.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The capacity of the concen-- of the gas chambers was 36,000.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there were days when they arrived more-- 40,000, 45,000 a day, you know, long cattle train, about 60 cattle trucks, in each one, about 50, 60 people.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's about 3,500 in one train.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was train after train after train, day and night.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When they cleaned the ghettos, for example, in Hungary-- I remember '44, June-- it was traffic like hell.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they, they increased the quantity of the Sonderkommando.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was a kommando consisted only of Jews who worked in the crematoriums.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They had a horrible job.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They had to take the people into the gas chamber, take the corpses from the gas chamber to the oven, dispose afterwards of the ashes, and this whole job.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And this was, when I arrived in '43, the group was about 50, 60 people like that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But it was only one crematorium working.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Afterwards, when it was four crematoriums, because the number one was Auschwitz, main camp, and two, three, four, and five was in Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The Sonderkommando was increased to 5- 600 people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, what's happened?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Some people, most of their people have been selected by force and sent to work in the Sonderkommando.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Only few volunteered to go, because it was better food.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they could organize something from the goods which the people brought with them to the gas chamber, and so.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But it was a rather, I would say, a risky business.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because from time to time, they have taken a group of Sonderkommando and sent to another camp, for example to Mauthausen or to another camp.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
